---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Sai Sri Ram Sribhashyam"
  description="Sai Sri Ram Sribhashyam — AI systems, labor markets, and digital public infrastructure across 30+ countries."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="about-main container">
    <div class="about-header">
      <div class="about-photo-placeholder" aria-label="Ram Sribhashyam">SR</div>
      <p class="about-name">Sai Sri Ram Sribhashyam</p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-body">
      <p class="about-para">
        I started as an engineer — BITS Pilani, mechanical and chemistry — and spent
        the first years of my career at Mu Sigma and Grameen Foundation building
        analytics systems and learning what it takes to turn data into decisions that
        actually change something. That brought me to the World Bank, where I spent
        twelve years working across Group Internal Audit, the Education Global
        Practice, and cross-functional analytics — overseeing $2B+ portfolios,
        building AI-powered monitoring systems, and leading the labor market analytics
        work that shaped policy across MENA, South Asia, and the Western Balkans.
        Most recently I was in Andhra Pradesh with the Tony Blair Institute, working
        directly with ministers and IAS officers to design the AI infrastructure for
        one of India's largest state governments.
      </p>

      <p class="about-para">
        The thread across all of it is the same problem: the gap between what people
        and institutions can do, and what systems can see and act on. Whether that's
        a University of Rwanda graduate with a Master's in IoT that no employer can
        verify, a labor market model that fails Arabic-speaking workers because the
        training data was thinner there, or a government ministry that has the mandate
        but not the architecture to deliver at scale — the work is always about closing
        that gap. I'm relocating to San Francisco and looking for the next place to do
        that — at the intersection of AI systems, real-world institutions, and the
        people they're supposed to serve.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
.about-main {
  padding: 6rem 0 var(--space-24);
  max-width: 640px;
}
.about-header {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: var(--space-4);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
}
.about-photo-placeholder {
  width: 96px;
  height: 96px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--color-accent-light);
  color: var(--color-accent);
  font-size: var(--text-xl);
  font-weight: 500;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}
.about-name {
  font-size: var(--text-base);
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}
.about-body {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--space-8);
}
.about-para {
  font-size: var(--text-base);
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.75;
}
</style>
